href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00QD</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Second, enable <fr:code>format=flowed</fr:code> using the following completely undocumented command:</fr:p><fr:pre>defaults write com.freron.MailMate MmFormatFlowedEnabled -bool true</fr:pre><fr:p>Note that this option is so undocumented that it does not even appear in the list of <fr:link
type="external"
href="https://manual.mailmate-app.com/hidden_preferences.html">hidden preferences</fr:link>. There is some discussion of this on the <fr:link
type="external"
href="https://lists.freron.com/mailmate/2021-May/014194.html">mailing list</fr:link>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:p>Although the <fr:link
type="external"
href="https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3676.txt"><fr:code>format=flowed</fr:code> standard</fr:link> standard is very rarely implemented by clients, email sent using this flag will be formatted correctly by <fr:link
type="external"
href="https://lists.sr.ht/">SourceHut Lists</fr:link>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>